WEBVTT

00:03:56.966 --> 00:04:01.133
But the ability to retain and recall
information in your head is still crucial.

00:04:01.157 --> 00:04:03.323
(Music)

00:04:03.347 --> 00:04:06.703
One: it helps you establish
expertise under uncertainty.

00:04:07.228 --> 00:04:10.791
If a car salesperson knows safety specs
off the top of her head,

00:04:10.815 --> 00:04:13.156
you'll assume she knows
what she's talking about.

00:04:14.085 --> 00:04:17.951
Two: having a good memory
is essential for making fast decisions.

00:04:18.379 --> 00:04:21.450
When a patient goes into cardiac arrest
during a procedure,

00:04:21.474 --> 00:04:24.674
surgeons don't have time
to run a Google search about what to do.

00:04:25.887 --> 00:04:29.355
And three: memory helps you
build and maintain relationships.

00:04:29.998 --> 00:04:33.228
You expect a financial planner
to remember your risk preferences.